Among them is the Museum of Israel, located near the Knesset (Israeli Parliament).
It preserves the ancient Manuscripts of the Dead Sea or Rollos of Qumran, discovered in the caves of the Jewish desert, and about 500 thousand archaeological and anthropological pieces.
It is worth visiting the Museum of Art in Tel Aviv.
