In Acre you can visit the Al Basha Bathroom Museum, which are some old Turkish bathrooms rooms with model figures of visitors and bathers of that time.
In Cesarea it is worth going through the exclusive Ralli private museum, where you can admire the sculptures of Rodin and Dalí.
There are no tourist guides or souvenir shops there.
The entry is free, and categorically no donations are accepted.
The fifth, the Holocaust Museum or Yad Vashem in Tel Aviv, shows one of the most dramatic pages in history.
The most tragic section is the Memorial of Children, built in memory of the 1.5 million children killed in concentration camps and gas chambers.
