The problem that may arise is that the regulation "strengthens" and that it is impossible to comply with it.
Already under the previous regulations, the controlled persons were linked to the contractor (e.g. in the case of regional operational programmes of the Regional Council), and each unrespected law on public procurement meant the violation of budgetary discipline.
Does it make sense then to harden the law this way?
