To help measure it, some researchers in the 1980s developed a "scale of tendency to boredom".
The scale includes issues such as "many of the things I have to do are repetitive and monotonous" and "there are so many things I'm interested in that I don't have time to do everything."
Stephen Vodanovich, professor of Psychology at West Florida University, says that, using these scales, researchers have found that boys tend to get bored more often than girls, and specifically need more external and more varied stimulation.
