Ends Unasur Summit without making public the Lima Declaration
The Sixth Presidential Summit of the South American Union of Nations (Unasur) concluded today in Peru without the publication of the Lima Declaration, previously announced and theoretically subscribed by the seven assistant delegates.
Effect repeatedly attempted to access the signed document at the VI Ordinary Meeting of Heads of State and Government of Unasur, but sources of Chancellor and Presidency noted at a start that would deliver it after the closure, but then stated that it would be published at some point on the Peruvian Government website.
