During the day, only the soundless video of the presidential assembly was transmitted in the press room with the message "private session, restricted audio".
The little information that circulated among the reporters was delivered by the press spokespersons of some of the Unasur governments attending the appointment, although not Peruvian.
The only document released during the day was the list of assistant presidents, which caused the discomfort of hundreds of journalists from various national and international media who asked for more data.
Subsequently, the Presidency of Peru sent an e-mail to the media with the "final declaration" of the summit, but this is the statement by Humala, not the official document that closed the summit.
